2.00	Jack_Yeovil	Kim Newman	Kim Newman (born 31 July 1959) is an English journalist, film critic, and fiction writer. Recurring interests visible in his work include film history and horror fiction—both of which he attributes to seeing Tod Browning's Dracula at the age of eleven—and alternate fictional versions of history. He has won the Bram Stoker Award, the International Horror Guild Award, and the BSFA award.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/31/Kim_Newman.jpg/220px-Kim_Newman.jpg
